  "claim_boundary": "A finite-size, finite-time measurement of the 1+1d KPZ exponents and of which Tracy-Widom law each geometry's fluctuations sit nearer. The effective beta = 0.3127 sits 0.0207 BELOW the exact 1/3 — the documented preasymptotic approach from below. That this is the finite fit window and not a defect in the KPZ measurement is evidenced by the Edwards-Wilkinson control, which misses its own exact 1/4 by 0.0146 in the SAME direction, while random deposition — which has no correlation time to be preasymptotic about — lands at 0.5003 against an exact 1/2. The distributional claim is CLASS ASSIGNMENT by skewness — a shape statistic invariant under the unfitted (v_inf, Gamma) rescaling — and NOT a full Tracy-Widom distribution collapse. Measured moment gaps this run: droplet/GUE: skewness 0.0590 from target (1.9x its sampling sigma), excess kurtosis 0.1061 from target (1.7x); flat/GOE: skewness 0.0203 from target (1.3x its sampling sigma), excess kurtosis 0.0089 from target (0.3x) (sampled at 24000 points, 4.7 correlation lengths apart, so this sigma is a floor). The kurtosis is carried as evidence and is deliberately NOT graded by check_m17. Nothing here claims the Tracy-Widom constants v_inf or Gamma, which are not measured, nor the exponents' asymptotic values, which this window cannot reach.",
